### Anything else relevant?

I tested with an older version of Angular CLI, specifically v20.0.3 (before commit [2316fe2](https://github.com/angular/angular-cli/commit/2316fe2)), and the issue did not occur there.

As a workaround, I added an additional overrides entry in `package.json` to explicitly force Prettier to use single quotes for `.ts` files:
```json
"prettier": {
    "overrides": [
      {
        "files": "*.html",
        "options": {
          "parser": "angular"
        }
      },
      {
        "files": "*.ts",
        "options": {
          "singleQuote": true
        }
      }
    ]
  }
```

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6fb00327-1580-4618-89d3-0fd7c858860c)

This seems to restore the expected formatting behavior for TypeScript files, though I’m not certain whether this workaround could introduce unintended side effects. Further testing would be helpful.

